6 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
7 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
8 Article – Natural Resources
9 10–206.
10 (A) The Department may reduce the wildlife population in any county, election
11 district, or other identifiable area of the State after a thorough investigation reveals that
12 protected wildlife is seriously injurious to agricultural or other interests in the affected
13 area. The method of reducing the wildlife population is at the Department’s discretion,
14 except that trapping is preferred whenever feasible. The Department shall dispose of
15 wildlife taken pursuant to the provisions of this section as the Department deems
16 advisable.
17 (B) (1) IN THIS SUBSECTION, “DEER DAMAGE” INCLUDES:
18 (I) WIDESPREAD DAMAGE CAUSED BY DEER, INCLUDING THE
19 ELIMINATION OF FOREST UNDERSTORY, TREE REGENERATION, AND NATIVE
20 PLANTS; AND
21 (II) THE DESTRUCTION OF AGRICULTURAL CROPS OR
22 LANDSCAPING, INCLUDING ORNAMENTAL LANDSCAPING, CAUSED BY DEER.
23 (2) THE DEPARTMENT MAY AUTHORIZE THE REDUCTION OF THE
24 DEER POPULATION ON ANY SINGLE, CONTIGUOUS PROPERTY OF AT LEAST 10 ACRES
25 WHERE THE DEPARTMENT HAS DOCUMENTED DEER DAMAGE.
26 (3) (I) THE METHOD OF REDUCING THE DEER POPULATION:
27 1. IS AT THE DEPARTMENT’S DISCRETION; AND
28 2. SUBJECT TO SUBPARAGRAPH (II) OF THIS
29 PARAGRAPH, MAY INCLUDE THE ISSUANCE OF A PERMIT TO A PROPERTY OWNER, OR
30 THE PROPERTY OWNER’S EMPLOYEE, LESSEE, OR AGENT, TO SHOOT DEER ON THE
31 PROPERTY ON SUNDAYS.
32 (II) A PERMIT ISSUED UNDER SUBPARAGRAPH (I)2 OF THIS
33 PARAGRAPH SHALL:

SENATE BILL 643 3
1 1. MAY NOT AUTHORIZE HUNTING ON SUNDAYS IN:
2 A. BALTIMORE CITY;
3 B. BALTIMORE COUNTY;
4 C. HOWARD COUNTY; OR
5 D. PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY; AND
6 2. SHALL PROHIBIT DEER HUNTING ON SUNDAYS
7 DURING DEER FIREARMS SEASON WITHIN 25 150 YARDS OF A DEPARTMENT TRAIL
8 DESIGNATED FOR BICYCLING, HIKING, EQUESTRIAN USE, OR OTHER ACTIVE OR
9 PASSIVE RECREATIONAL USE.
10 (4) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL:
11 (I) MAP AREAS OF THE STATE TO WHICH A PERMIT MAY APPLY
12 UNDER THIS SUBSECTION; AND
13 (II) MAKE THE MAPS READILY AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC.
