16 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, on or before December 1,
17 2029, the Department of Natural Resources shall:
18 (1) report to the General Assembly, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the
19 State Government Article, on the effectiveness of this Act on deer management and
20 balancing stakeholder interests; and
21 (2) include in the report input from all relevant stakeholders That:
22 (a) The Department of Natural Resources shall, in accordance with this section,
23 report annually on the impact of this Act on deer management in the State, the safety of
24 hunters and other individuals who engage in outdoor recreation, and the balancing of
25 stakeholder interests.
26 (b) Reports made under this section shall include:
27 (1) a summary of any regulations adopted under § 10–410(a)(1) of the
28 Natural Resources Article, as enacted by Section 2 of this Act, during the reporting period;
29 (2) data regarding hunting related accidents;
30 (3) summaries of complaints received from any source regarding conflicts
31 between hunters and other individuals engaging in outdoor recreation; and

16 SENATE BILL 643
1 (4) any recommendations from the Department on strategies to improve
2 safety or decrease conflicts.
3 (c) On or before December 1, 2027, December 1, 2028, and December 1, 2029, the
4 Department shall, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the State Government Article, submit
5 the reports required under this section to the Senate Committee on Education, Energy, and
6 the Environment and the House Environment and Transportation Committee.
7 SECTION 4. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act may not be construed
8 to authorize the Department of Natural Resources to allow Sunday hunting in Baltimore
9 County, Howard County, or Prince George’s County:
10 (1) (i) except as provided in Section 10–410(a)(9) through (11) of the
11 Natural Resources Article, as enacted by Section 1 of this Act; and
12 (ii) subject to Section 10–410(a)(8) of the Natural Resources Article,
13 as enacted by Section 1 of this Act; or
14 (2) (i) except as provided in Section 10–410(a)(3) through (5) of the
15 Natural Resources Article, as enacted by Section 2 of this Act; and
16 (ii) subject to Section 10–410(a)(2) of the Natural Resources Article,
17 as enacted by Section 2 of this Act.
18 SECTION 5. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That Section 2 of this Act shall take
19 effect July 1, 2027. It shall remain effective for a period of 3 years and, at the end of June
20 30, 2030, Section 2 of this Act, with no further action required by the General Assembly,
21 shall be abrogated and of no further force and effect.
22 SECTION 5. 6. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, except as provided in
23 Section 4 5 of this Act, this Act shall take effect July 1, 2026.
